headline: Dell Technologies Powers TACC's New Supercomputer Horizon
summary: ROUND ROCK, Texas, November 17, 2025--Dell Technologies (NYSE: DELL) is working with The University of Texas at Austin’s TACC and NVIDIA to build Horizon, the largest academic supercomputer in the U.S. Horizon will serve as a platform for open science and scientific research, advancing progress and discovery for the next generation of researchers in areas like national security, healthcare and climate science.

headline: Dell Stock Gets a Double Downgrade. Why J.P. Morgan Says Buy.
summary: Dell Technologies  stock slumped following a double downgrade from analysts at  Morgan Stanley  even though another bank counseled investors to buy the stock ahead of next week’s earnings report.  Morgan Stanley slashed its rating for Dell stock to Underweight from Overweight and lowered its price target to $110 from $144 in a research note Sunday.  A surge in the price of memory drives—a component in Dell products like servers and PCs—will weigh on Dell’s margins, it said.
